{"key":"processedPost-8570536","value":{"id":8570536,"first":8569733,"last":8573161,"when":1214583455,"utime":"06/27/08 07:17 PM","content":"Old tek.&nbsp; You don't want your cake to have a steady moisture content.&nbsp; It's important to mimick natural cycles to get the best harvest.&nbsp; A substrate will perform better if it slightly dries out, and then gets rehydrated.&nbsp; Wicking type systems have been tried lots of times with limited success, because one of the secondary pinning triggers is evaporation of moisture from the substrate.<br />RR","title":"Re: Why I didnt saw ppl doing this TEK?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}